# Content Creation Guidelines

## Blog Posts
When creating new blog posts in [_posts/](mdc:_posts/):
- Use filename format: `YYYY-MM-DD-title.markdown`
- Include required front matter:
  ```yaml
  ---
  layout: single
  title: "Post Title"
  date: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS -0700
  tags: tag1 tag2
  ---
  ```
- Posts automatically use `single` layout with author profile enabled (configured in [_config.yml](mdc:_config.yml) defaults)

## Pages
When creating pages in [_pages/](mdc:_pages/):
- Use descriptive filenames ending in `.markdown`
- Include permalink in front matter for custom URLs
- Common layouts: `single`, `splash`, `archive`
- Add to [_data/navigation.yml](mdc:_data/navigation.yml) if needed in main menu

## Front Matter Standards
- Always include `layout` (single, splash, archive, etc.)
- Use `title` for page/post titles
- Use `permalink` for custom URLs on pages
- Use `header` section for overlay images and actions
- Portfolio uses `classes: wide` for full-width layout

## Image Management
- Store images in [assets/images/](mdc:assets/images/)
- Use descriptive filenames
- Reference with `/assets/images/filename.jpg`
- Banner images: networking-banner.jpg, work-banner.jpg, blog-banner.jpg